{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between PR-change discovery and file-analysis selection. A unit test of filtering logic alone can miss wiring mistakes (wrong file list source, path normalization mismatch, or selector not applied). No real OS/network is strictly required for the minimum failure-catching test if modules are wired with local fixtures.","test_description":"Run the analysis step against a fixture repo state and a stubbed PR-changed-files provider that returns a mixed set; execute real analyzer-selection wiring and assert analyzer invocations occur only for changed paths and never for unchanged paths.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real risk is at module boundaries: linter result objects -> grouping/renderer -> PR comment payload. A pure unit test on formatter logic can miss schema/field mapping mismatches that break grouping in the posted output. Real GitHub API is not required for minimum detection.","test_description":"Execute the comment-building pipeline with multi-severity findings from the real result model, then assert the final outbound comment body contains correctly grouped sections and entries under error/warning/info before the posting client boundary.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a runtime/performance SLA tied to GitHub Actions timeout and process execution characteristics. Mocked timing or mocked linter execution can hide real bottlenecks (process startup cost, filesystem traversal, CPU contention). Requires real subprocess/OS behavior.","test_description":"Run the actual pipeline entrypoint in a CI-like environment on a generated 200-file fixture PR diff, with real linter subprocess execution and wall-clock measurement; assert completion under 10 minutes including comment generation path.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The behavior explicitly depends on real subprocess crash semantics and recovery. Simulating an exception in-process may not reproduce exit codes, partial output, or stream handling failures. Mocking the process can hide true crash-handling regressions.","test_description":"Invoke the pipeline with real linter subprocess execution on a file set containing one intentionally malformed file that triggers a process crash for that file; assert subsequent files are still analyzed and a final PR comment payload is produced with surviving findings plus crash note.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The failure is primarily deterministic deduplication logic over finding keys (file, line, rule/signature). No I/O or module handoff is inherently required to expose this bug if inputs are directly constructed.","test_description":"Call the deduplication function with synthetic findings containing intentional same-line overlaps from different rule emitters and assert only one output record per dedupe key while preserving expected severity/message precedence.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
